-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Effigies source code in this repository is licensed under MIT (above).
Effigies is an orchestration layer: it invokes the projects below as separate
programs, and the Docker image bundles them as an aggregation. Each retains its
own license, which continues to govern that component:

  NodeODM, ODM   — AGPL-3.0     (https://github.com/OpenDroneMap)
  OpenMVS        — AGPL-3.0     (https://github.com/cdcseacave/openMVS)
  COLMAP         — BSD-3-Clause (https://github.com/colmap/colmap)
  OpenSfM        — BSD-2-Clause (https://github.com/mapillary/OpenSfM)

If you redistribute the Docker image (or any build that bundles the AGPL-3.0
components above), the AGPL-3.0 obligations apply to those components — in
particular, you must make their corresponding source available to users who
interact with them over a network. Effigies uses these components unmodified,
so that obligation is satisfied by pointing to their upstream repositories.
See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md for details.
